<br>
All I wanted from my original post was some clarification.  Is the Fed going to be hard-core Fed only?  Or will they &quot;open their arms&quot; to other people they consider friends?  And will this extent on an encompassing basis, or will guilds be able to choose their own policy?  I just want those questions answered, so I know whether or not to bother signing up for Fed raids.<br>
<br>
In regards to loot, I have similar priorities as Vigdis and others.  My guild comes first.  Thus why we have the first 2 drops reserved.  However, the rest are open to any who attend.  Heck, on our Monday night Kael Raid, our only 2 drops (chain gloves + plate bracer) went to 2 non-guildies who were attending.  And I don't have any qualms about it.<br>
<br>
I'd actually prefer to see the Federation reserving items for themselves on raids, instead of just going to a closed door policy.  For one, I really don't attend (or try to attend) your raids with the purpose of getting loot.  I like to attend your raids because they're run well (and thus I learn), and the people that attend them are people I enjoy hanging out with.  In most cases, I would turn down loot in preference to Fed members.<br>
<br>
A little clarification on the Federation's policies is all I ask.  Might help keep that shiny image that people respect even shinier.<br>
<br>
-Yarrick<br>
