Hehe, I freely admit that I would LOVE to have a fraction of the items they have. But I never will. Why? Because I choose my friends and loved ones over the faceless masses it takes to do that kind of stuff.<br>
<br>
I admit it, I get jealous of them sometimes. Do I get jealous because they are willing and able to put in the time/effort/sacrifice/single-minded focus? No. I get jealous because those are some DAMNED nice items. But do I codemn them for the choices they make? Once again, nope. Our paths are for us to chose and to hell with anybody who would try to tell us how to live our lives.<br>
<br>
So what AM I condemning? I condemn those who put the negative connotation on the word &quot;uber&quot; just because they aren't _willing_ to put in the sacrifice that it takes to go out and get the stuff that they /drool about.<br>
<br>
